               <interp inst="t17371207-2" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17371207"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17371207-2" type="date" value="17371207"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17371207-2-off9-c31" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-defend33 t17371207-2-off9 t17371207-2-verdict12"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17371207-2-off9-c32" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-defend35 t17371207-2-off9 t17371207-2-verdict12"></join>
         
               <p>3, 4. 
               
                  <persName id="t17371207-2-defend33" type="defendantName">
                     Jonathan 
                     Jordan 
                  <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend33" type="surname" value="Jordan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend33" type="given" value="Jonathan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend33" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t17371207-2-defend35" type="defendantName">
                     Robert 
                     Steppen 
                  <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend35" type="surname" value="Steppen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend35" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-defend35" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
             of <placeName id="t17371207-2-defloc8">St. Andrew Undershaft</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17371207-2-defloc8" type="placeName" value="St. Andrew Undershaft"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17371207-2-defloc8" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-defend33 t17371207-2-defloc8"></join>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-defend35 t17371207-2-defloc8"></join>, were indicted for <rs id="t17371207-2-off9" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-off9" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-off9" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               feloniously making and forging, and causing to be made and forged a certain Promissory Note for the Payment of 3 l. 6 s. in the Words following, viz. I promise to pay unto Jonathan Jordan or Order, the Sum of 3 l. 6 s. on Demand for Value received, per me, 
                     <persName id="t17371207-2-person36">
                        James 
                        Smith 
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-person36" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371207-2-person36" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371207-2-person36" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  . Test. Robert Steppen. With Intent to defraud the said 
                     <persName id="t17371207-2-victim37" type="victimName">
                        James 
                        Smith 
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-victim37" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371207-2-victim37" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371207-2-victim37" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-off9 t17371207-2-victim37"></join>
                     </persName>
                    of the Parish of St. George in the East, <rs id="t17371207-2-viclabel10" type="occupation">Mariner</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-victim37 t17371207-2-viclabel10"></join>, of the said Sum of 3 l. 6 s. against the Peace of our Sovereign Lord the King, &amp;c. And likewise against the Form of the Statute, &amp;c. And the said Jordan and Steppen, on the said <rs id="t17371207-2-cd11" type="crimeDate">10th of Oct.</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371207-2-off9 t17371207-2-cd11"></join> the abovesaid Promissory Note did utter and publish as true, they well knowing the same to be false, forged and counterfeit
            </rs>. The Jury <rs id="t17371207-2-verdict12" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17371207-2-verdict12" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs> the Prisoners, and the Court ordered Steppen a Copy of his Indictment.</p>
            </div1>
